<!-- ── HOW IT WORKS ── -->
<section class="py-12 lg:py-20 px-4 bg-base-300/30" id="telling-how" aria-labelledby="telling-how-heading">
  <div class="max-w-screen-lg mx-auto">
    <p class="text-xs font-semibold tracking-widest uppercase text-primary mb-3">How It Works</p>
    <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight text-base-content serif-bold mb-4" id="telling-how-heading">Three lines of code.<br/>A universe of voices.</h2>
    <p class="text-lg text-base-content/70 max-w-xl mb-12">
      Add Bonfire Telling to any blog, documentation site, or static page.
      Comments flow through the fediverse and appear as threads on your site.
    </p>
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
      <div class="bg-base-content/10 rounded-2xl p-8 hover:bg-base-content/5 transition-all">
        <div class="w-9 h-9 rounded-full bg-primary/10 text-primary flex items-center justify-center serif-bold text-lg mb-4">1</div>
        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-base-content mb-2">Embed the iframe</h3>
        <p class="text-base text-base-content/70">Paste a single HTML snippet into your page template. Bonfire Telling widget loads in an iframe, fully styled and self-contained — no JavaScript bundles, no build steps.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-base-content/10 rounded-2xl p-8 hover:bg-base-content/5 transition-all">
        <div class="w-9 h-9 rounded-full bg-primary/10 text-primary flex items-center justify-center serif-bold text-lg mb-4">2</div>
        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-base-content mb-2">Readers join from anywhere</h3>
        <p class="text-base text-base-content/70">Visitors reply using their Bonfire, Mastodon, Pleroma, or any ActivityPub-compatible account. No new signups. No platform lock-in. Their identity travels with them.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-base-content/10 rounded-2xl p-8 hover:bg-base-content/5 transition-all">
        <div class="w-9 h-9 rounded-full bg-primary/10 text-primary flex items-center justify-center serif-bold text-lg mb-4">3</div>
        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-base-content mb-2">Conversations federate</h3>
        <p class="text-base text-base-content/70">Every comment is an ActivityPub post. Replies flow back to the commenter's timeline, their followers can engage, and the whole thread stays visible on your site.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

